WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:03.080
<i>Previously on Will Trent.</i>

2
00:00:03.170 --> 00:00:04.370
Are you going to Caleb's tonight?

3
00:00:04.460 --> 00:00:06.460
I don't know. His family is loud.

4
00:00:06.540 --> 00:00:09.670
Did you know sharks don't have any bones?
They only have cartilage.

5
00:00:09.760 --> 00:00:11.510
Really?

6
00:00:13.260 --> 00:00:14.970
James Ulster has a big head start.

7
00:00:15.050 --> 00:00:17.140
We know that Ulster
is well-connected and charming.

8
00:00:17.220 --> 00:00:19.850
It's possible that he's using people
to help him. and we want to know who.

9
00:00:19.930 --> 00:00:21.980
Now. Ulster's had two fiancées.

10
00:00:22.060 --> 00:00:24.650
- That two-timing...
- Asshole.

11
00:00:24.730 --> 00:00:26.560
Is it possible that there's a third?

12
00:00:26.650 --> 00:00:31.030
This man dictated my whole life
from the moment I was born.

13
00:00:31.110 --> 00:00:32.360
I have to end this.

14
00:00:32.440 --> 00:00:33.530
What happened?

15
00:00:33.610 --> 00:00:34.910
Ulster took him from his day camp.

16
00:00:34.990 --> 00:00:37.740
and then. according to Calvin.
Uncle Will traded places with him.

17
00:00:40.160 --> 00:00:41.160
Time to die.

18
00:01:10.610 --> 00:01:11.690
What do you have for me?

19
00:01:12.190 --> 00:01:15.400
Arson investigators said there was
a lot of accelerant in the vehicle.

20
00:01:15.490 --> 00:01:17.740
All signs point to murder-suicide.

21
00:01:18.240 --> 00:01:20.200
Hey. Pete. Just say it.

22
00:01:20.280 --> 00:01:23.870
I can't make an official determination
yet. but both bodies are male.

23
00:01:24.620 --> 00:01:26.080
Initial assessments are consistent

24
00:01:26.160 --> 00:01:30.040
with what we expect
for James Ulster and Special Agent Trent.

25
00:01:31.340 --> 00:01:33.090
We'll work as fast as possible.

26
00:01:45.350 --> 00:01:46.350
I wanna see.

27
00:01:58.450 --> 00:02:00.740
Angie. we're still processing the scene.

28
00:02:00.820 --> 00:02:02.080
Pete. let her.

29
00:02:09.500 --> 00:02:11.000
Something fused to his chest.

30
00:02:14.050 --> 00:02:15.090
What is this?

31
00:02:17.420 --> 00:02:18.430
Is that a…

32
00:02:19.680 --> 00:02:20.720
a flip phone?

33
00:02:24.810 --> 00:02:25.890
It's not Will's.

34
00:02:26.600 --> 00:02:28.440
He hasn't used this in over a year.

35
00:02:28.520 --> 00:02:32.400
Pete. Will wears a gold medallion.
his mother's necklace.

36
00:02:32.480 --> 00:02:33.860
Did you find anything?

37
00:02:33.940 --> 00:02:35.190
We didn't find any jewelry.

38
00:02:35.280 --> 00:02:37.400
- You sure?
- Yeah.

39
00:02:37.490 --> 00:02:39.610
It's not him. It's not Will.

40
00:02:39.700 --> 00:02:41.490
The other body's not gonna be
Ulster either.

41
00:02:41.570 --> 00:02:42.570
This was staged.

42
00:02:42.660 --> 00:02:45.040
Ulster was trying to distract us.
slow us down.

43
00:02:45.120 --> 00:02:46.790
but he didn't know
that Will switched phones.

44
00:02:46.870 --> 00:02:48.370
Will could still be alive.

45
00:02:48.460 --> 00:02:49.710
That's good enough for me.

46
00:02:49.790 --> 00:02:51.080
Let's go find him.

47
00:02:51.170 --> 00:02:53.840
I'll tell the marshals
to keep the roadblocks up.

48
00:03:26.200 --> 00:03:28.250
Time to die.

49
00:03:40.010 --> 00:03:42.050
Now you get your keys.

50
00:03:44.640 --> 00:03:45.640
Watch out.

51
00:04:23.090 --> 00:04:26.510
Will. I can't feel my legs.

52
00:04:28.100 --> 00:04:29.770
You don't need them anymore.

53
00:04:29.850 --> 00:04:31.220
Come… Come on. Will.

54
00:04:31.890 --> 00:04:33.350
This isn't like you…

55
00:04:39.690 --> 00:04:41.990
In 100 feet. turn right.

56
00:04:43.610 --> 00:04:44.740
Turn right.

57
00:04:49.740 --> 00:04:51.660
You have missed the turn.

58
00:04:51.750 --> 00:04:53.250
To reach GBI headquarters...

59
00:04:53.330 --> 00:04:55.210
Eduardo. cancel directions.

60
00:04:55.290 --> 00:04:57.630
Would you like to set a new destination?

61
00:05:00.710 --> 00:05:02.420
Where are you going. Will?

62
00:05:02.510 --> 00:05:04.420
Where are you going. Will?

63
00:05:05.010 --> 00:05:06.550
Where are you going. Will?

64
00:05:06.640 --> 00:05:08.350
I don't know. Eduardo.

65
00:05:09.760 --> 00:05:11.770
I've got the bad guy.
but I gotta tell you.

66
00:05:12.970 --> 00:05:14.680
I don't feel like bringing him in.

67
00:05:14.770 --> 00:05:16.390
Hey. who you talking to?

68
00:05:16.480 --> 00:05:18.900
It sounds like you are taking
the law into your own hands.

69
00:05:20.480 --> 00:05:21.480
Maybe.

70
00:05:23.240 --> 00:05:25.450
Maybe I'm not done with him just yet.

71
00:05:25.530 --> 00:05:28.200
Will. I can't feel my leg.

72
00:05:28.280 --> 00:05:29.280
I'm clotting.

73
00:05:47.930 --> 00:05:49.090
Get any sleep?

74
00:05:49.800 --> 00:05:52.720
Good morning. What can I do for you?

75
00:05:52.810 --> 00:05:53.930
Well. we have a problem.

76
00:05:54.020 --> 00:05:58.810
You assigned GBI man power to a search
that I already passed off to the marshals.

77
00:05:58.900 --> 00:06:00.900
We're searching
for Special Agent Will Trent now.

78
00:06:00.980 --> 00:06:02.820
Yeah. you don't make that call. I do.

79
00:06:02.900 --> 00:06:05.070
We don't even have ID on the bodies yet.

80
00:06:05.150 --> 00:06:07.110
I was at the scene. I saw enough.

81
00:06:07.610 --> 00:06:09.360
And I made the call
because you were asleep.

82
00:06:09.450 --> 00:06:14.490
Amanda. this is chaos. okay?
Only one of us can be in charge here.

83
00:06:16.790 --> 00:06:19.500
Oh. look. I just ended my medical leave.

84
00:06:20.080 --> 00:06:21.080
Let's make it me.

85
00:06:21.170 --> 00:06:23.300
Wagner. stop. I want you to listen to me.

86
00:06:23.380 --> 00:06:25.960
I get it. You think I'm an empty suit.

87
00:06:26.050 --> 00:06:29.050
Well. I think
you're a fire-breathing HR violation.

88
00:06:29.130 --> 00:06:30.930
but I don't wanna see you hurt yourself.

89
00:06:31.010 --> 00:06:32.850
They're waiting for me in
the conference room. Bill.

90
00:06:32.930 --> 00:06:35.060
I'll have Caroline box up your things.

91
00:06:36.430 --> 00:06:41.020
This is Darren Torrenson. Roommate
of fiancée number three. Jackie Weggle.

92
00:06:41.100 --> 00:06:44.360
He went missing yesterday. and he's most
likely the dead body in the driver's seat.

93
00:06:44.440 --> 00:06:46.400
Makes sense.
He's a good body match for Ulster.

94
00:06:46.480 --> 00:06:49.990
Yup. and with strong confidence.
this is the passenger.

95
00:06:50.070 --> 00:06:52.870
He worked in an office a few blocks away
from Jackie Weggle's home.

96
00:06:52.950 --> 00:06:54.580
Didn't make it back past his lunch break.

97
00:06:55.080 --> 00:06:57.370
Ulster targeted him
because he's wearing the right suit.

98
00:06:57.450 --> 00:06:58.790
If Ulster staged all this.

99
00:06:58.870 --> 00:07:01.120
then it means.
he has a new plan to leave the country.

100
00:07:01.210 --> 00:07:03.790
Caleb's team has a location
on Will's Porsche.

101
00:07:03.880 --> 00:07:05.670
- What?
- It was abandoned at a gas station

102
00:07:05.750 --> 00:07:07.800
20 miles from here.
You're all getting the address right now.

103
00:07:07.880 --> 00:07:09.920
Be smart with your resources.

104
00:07:10.010 --> 00:07:12.180
Don't double up on leads
and coordinate with Ormewood.

105
00:07:12.260 --> 00:07:13.800
He's at everyone's disposal.

106
00:07:24.190 --> 00:07:25.270
We have this backwards.

107
00:07:26.070 --> 00:07:29.400
The hair. the blood back here.
Will had Ulster in custody.

108
00:07:29.490 --> 00:07:32.160
Car's here. Phone's here.
Where the hell is he?

109
00:07:43.630 --> 00:07:45.750
He had over half a tank.
He didn't need gas.

110
00:07:46.380 --> 00:07:47.750
Any idea what his code is?

111
00:07:48.510 --> 00:07:50.760
Try 1323. Betty's gotcha date.

112
00:07:50.840 --> 00:07:53.180
0630. the address of the group home.

113
00:07:53.260 --> 00:07:58.010
Uh… 7499? 1106? 1104?

114
00:07:58.100 --> 00:07:59.100
That's it.

115
00:08:00.020 --> 00:08:03.270
Stake an ex. Polaski.
That's our secret weapon of finding him.

116
00:08:07.900 --> 00:08:09.280
I just saw the one dude.

117
00:08:09.360 --> 00:08:12.860
He was troubled. stomping around.
yelling on the phone.

118
00:08:12.950 --> 00:08:14.820
- What was he yelling about?
- Wasn't my business.

119
00:08:14.910 --> 00:08:17.990
I closed our shop. did inventory.
When I came back. he was gone.

120
00:08:18.080 --> 00:08:19.540
You never thought to call the authorities?

121
00:08:19.620 --> 00:08:21.410
There's a methadone clinic
right up the road.

122
00:08:21.500 --> 00:08:25.290
I got crazies coming in here all the time.
I figured he was one. and he'd be back.

123
00:08:25.380 --> 00:08:27.040
We're gonna need your security footage.

124
00:08:27.130 --> 00:08:28.340
I just did a double.

125
00:08:29.170 --> 00:08:31.260
I'm out. Call my boss.

126
00:08:31.340 --> 00:08:34.050
Keep acting like a jackass. you're
gonna find out how long a day can be.

127
00:08:35.050 --> 00:08:36.930
Don't look at me. He's a sheriff.

128
00:08:37.010 --> 00:08:38.600
That badge means
he doesn't answer to anyone.

129
00:08:38.680 --> 00:08:41.390
He could impound your car.
throw you in jail.

130
00:08:41.470 --> 00:08:44.270
I was thinking more like a very public
arrest for child pornography.

131
00:08:44.350 --> 00:08:46.900
Oh. Sure. Well. that's a bold way to move.

132
00:08:46.980 --> 00:08:48.310
Okay. okay.

133
00:08:49.520 --> 00:08:50.530
God.

134
00:08:55.490 --> 00:08:57.030
There he is.

135
00:08:57.990 --> 00:08:59.200
What are you doing. Will?

136
00:08:59.280 --> 00:09:01.240
I'm not listening to you. okay?

137
00:09:01.330 --> 00:09:04.660
I actually pulled over to get a new phone.
One that stays out of my head.

138
00:09:06.170 --> 00:09:07.630
You were right. Will had Ulster.

139
00:09:07.710 --> 00:09:09.090
Where was he taking him?

140
00:09:09.170 --> 00:09:12.510
I'd like to remind you that you
are a pathologically scrupulous person.

141
00:09:12.590 --> 00:09:14.220
Yeah. well. people can change.

142
00:09:14.920 --> 00:09:17.090
Right. I bring him in. then what. huh?

143
00:09:17.180 --> 00:09:21.100
He escapes again. More people die.
Whose fault is that?

144
00:09:21.180 --> 00:09:23.560
- His.
- Wrong. It's mine.

145
00:09:24.230 --> 00:09:27.060
He's a virus. a predator. okay?

146
00:09:27.560 --> 00:09:30.400
And he's not gonna stop.
but I can end this now.

147
00:09:30.480 --> 00:09:33.440
Will. whatever you're
thinking of doing. don't.

148
00:09:33.530 --> 00:09:35.820
Unlike me. you have a conscience.

149
00:09:35.900 --> 00:09:37.450
No one's talking to you!

150
00:09:43.620 --> 00:09:44.950
Who's this lady now?

151
00:09:45.040 --> 00:09:48.120
Would you like me to begin
a to-do list for covering up a murder?

152
00:09:48.210 --> 00:09:50.790
Oh. let's be clear. it is not murder.

153
00:09:50.880 --> 00:09:54.460
If I kill James Ulster.
it is absolutely a form of self-defense.

154
00:09:55.090 --> 00:09:56.420
- Oh!
- Oh.

155
00:09:57.380 --> 00:10:00.930
Uh… No need to worry. ma'am.
Just an official GBI matter.

156
00:10:01.470 --> 00:10:02.470
Help!

157
00:10:04.390 --> 00:10:07.980
I… I know
this all must look and sound crazy.

158
00:10:08.060 --> 00:10:10.560
I'm actually transporting
a very dangerous criminal.

159
00:10:10.650 --> 00:10:12.610
- Hey. I need you to be quiet. all right?
- Help!

160
00:10:17.240 --> 00:10:18.490
Oh. my God.

161
00:10:18.570 --> 00:10:21.660
Hey. will you shut up?
You're scaring this poor lady over here.

162
00:10:22.870 --> 00:10:24.580
Help!

163
00:10:30.580 --> 00:10:32.540
- Jesus. Will.
- Oh! Yikes.

164
00:10:34.170 --> 00:10:35.550
The hell?

165
00:10:35.630 --> 00:10:36.630
They know each other?

166
00:10:38.380 --> 00:10:42.260
You almost ruined everything!
How could you let yourself get captured?

167
00:10:42.350 --> 00:10:45.970
Baby. it's fine. No one knows we're here.

168
00:10:47.310 --> 00:10:48.390
The plan is still good.

169
00:10:55.730 --> 00:10:57.650
She never shows her face to the camera.

170
00:10:57.740 --> 00:10:59.200
I can zoom in.

171
00:11:02.530 --> 00:11:03.870
Look out!

172
00:11:07.370 --> 00:11:10.920
We have no idea who she is.
and what she wants.

173
00:11:11.420 --> 00:11:12.710
They could be anywhere by now.

174
00:11:59.590 --> 00:12:02.720
- Hey. hey. hey. hey!
- Ow!

175
00:12:02.800 --> 00:12:04.390
Who's the woman. James?

176
00:12:06.100 --> 00:12:07.640
Her name is Susan.

177
00:12:07.720 --> 00:12:09.720
She is my loving fiancée.

178
00:12:13.690 --> 00:12:15.150
Where'd she take us. huh?

179
00:12:15.770 --> 00:12:19.940
She's taking me to the new
life of freedom I richly deserve.

180
00:12:20.030 --> 00:12:23.910
Oh. yeah? Then why'd she put
a stun cuff on your leg. huh?

181
00:12:27.530 --> 00:12:29.540
I'm sure she has some good reason.

182
00:12:30.580 --> 00:12:31.580
Let me handle this.

183
00:12:31.660 --> 00:12:34.000
I've got her wrapped around my finger.

184
00:12:36.830 --> 00:12:38.960
Susan. my angel.

185
00:12:39.050 --> 00:12:40.670
I know about the other women. Jimmy.

186
00:12:41.630 --> 00:12:42.840
They don't mean a thing.

187
00:12:42.920 --> 00:12:47.010
They were mere stepping stones
to our everlasting love.

188
00:12:47.100 --> 00:12:48.640
I'll explain when we get to Canada.

189
00:12:48.720 --> 00:12:50.680
Canada is canceled.

190
00:12:50.770 --> 00:12:53.850
Wrapped around your finger. huh? Hmm?

191
00:12:54.770 --> 00:12:56.150
- We might have a problem.
- Mmm.

192
00:13:13.080 --> 00:13:16.870
If you'd just stayed
on the road and taken me into the GBI.

193
00:13:16.960 --> 00:13:19.130
If you had just stayed
in prison to begin with.

194
00:13:30.050 --> 00:13:31.060
Hi. boys.

195
00:13:31.140 --> 00:13:35.770
I popped things off on the lowest setting
so we can all agree on who's in charge.

196
00:13:35.850 --> 00:13:37.190
Anyone pee themselves?

197
00:13:37.270 --> 00:13:38.480
Yes? No?

198
00:13:39.900 --> 00:13:43.440
Hi. um. Ms. Susan.

199
00:13:43.530 --> 00:13:46.150
I'm Special Agent Will Trent
with the GBI. Um…

200
00:13:46.700 --> 00:13:49.620
Could the two of us
just have a one on one?

201
00:13:49.700 --> 00:13:50.740
Not interested.

202
00:13:51.370 --> 00:13:52.370
Back of the trailer.

203
00:13:53.370 --> 00:13:54.950
Come on.

204
00:14:00.840 --> 00:14:04.880
This little fellow goes to 11.
which will stop your heart.

205
00:14:04.960 --> 00:14:07.550
You've always been
in charge of my heart. my...

206
00:14:07.630 --> 00:14:09.890
Spare me the sugar-talk. Jimmy.

207
00:14:12.930 --> 00:14:15.850
Here. Clean yourselves up.

208
00:14:15.930 --> 00:14:17.940
Had to be a dribble or two. huh?

209
00:14:18.020 --> 00:14:21.060
I'll be back in two shakes
of a dog's butt.

210
00:14:21.560 --> 00:14:22.570
Bzz.

211
00:14:23.400 --> 00:14:25.570
Just kidding. Got you.

212
00:14:40.170 --> 00:14:41.290
- Turn around.
- What?

213
00:14:41.380 --> 00:14:43.090
You turn around.

214
00:14:50.890 --> 00:14:52.600
So. Jimmy.

215
00:14:53.640 --> 00:14:54.760
What's your plan?

216
00:14:55.640 --> 00:14:58.310
When the door opens. we rush her.

217
00:14:58.980 --> 00:15:00.060
You hold her down.

218
00:15:00.940 --> 00:15:03.520
I'll rip her throat out with my teeth.

219
00:15:04.020 --> 00:15:05.020
I'm never doing that.

220
00:15:05.110 --> 00:15:06.530
Please. don't act all superior.

221
00:15:06.610 --> 00:15:07.650
You were gonna kill me.

222
00:15:08.650 --> 00:15:10.150
I should have kept my head.

223
00:15:10.240 --> 00:15:12.320
I'd be home with my dog right now.

224
00:15:12.410 --> 00:15:15.490
I'm just saying. a throat rip can
be a real problem-solver

225
00:15:15.580 --> 00:15:17.330
and your dog isn't feeding itself.

226
00:15:17.410 --> 00:15:20.160
You know. I really do hope that
part of her plan involves hurting you.

227
00:15:23.670 --> 00:15:25.670
So. it's to be death by humiliation.

228
00:15:28.300 --> 00:15:30.130
Come on.

229
00:15:31.840 --> 00:15:33.260
Almost there.

230
00:15:34.680 --> 00:15:35.810
Go on.

231
00:15:35.890 --> 00:15:37.100
Hustle. come on.

232
00:15:42.980 --> 00:15:43.980
Go on.

233
00:15:49.030 --> 00:15:50.190
What the hell is this?

234
00:15:51.240 --> 00:15:52.320
Home.

235
00:15:53.610 --> 00:15:54.820
Have a seat.

236
00:16:06.590 --> 00:16:09.630
You don't expect me to eat this?

237
00:16:09.710 --> 00:16:12.380
That is a complete holiday meal.

238
00:16:12.470 --> 00:16:16.300
Turkey. turkey dressing.
veggie. tater cake.

239
00:16:16.390 --> 00:16:17.560
It's gray.

240
00:16:18.560 --> 00:16:20.470
It's… it's great.

241
00:16:20.560 --> 00:16:25.900
Um. and this. this is a lovely room.

242
00:16:26.400 --> 00:16:27.480
It's very warm.

243
00:16:28.230 --> 00:16:30.780
Did you do all this yourself?

244
00:16:31.530 --> 00:16:32.530
Yes.

245
00:16:36.700 --> 00:16:38.780
That's… It's impressive.

246
00:16:38.870 --> 00:16:42.160
It's a space that you feel
like you can settle into.

247
00:16:43.040 --> 00:16:44.040
Thank you.

248
00:16:46.080 --> 00:16:48.420
- I love interior design.
- Mm.

249
00:16:48.500 --> 00:16:49.590
That's what I had in mind.

250
00:16:50.460 --> 00:16:53.630
- Oh.
- I'd be honored to say grace.

251
00:16:54.880 --> 00:16:56.220
If you'd like?

252
00:17:02.640 --> 00:17:04.060
Well. go on then.

253
00:17:06.190 --> 00:17:07.190
Jimmy.

254
00:17:14.530 --> 00:17:16.780
Bless us. O Lord. and these thy gifts

255
00:17:16.860 --> 00:17:19.870
which we are about to receive
from thy bounty

256
00:17:19.950 --> 00:17:21.160
through Christ. our Lord.

257
00:17:21.240 --> 00:17:23.330
Yeah. hang on a second. bud.
Let me finish this search.

258
00:17:23.410 --> 00:17:25.580
How come you can use AI
to look up license plates.

259
00:17:25.670 --> 00:17:26.870
but I can't use it for my homework?

260
00:17:26.960 --> 00:17:28.880
Well. let me know
when your homework is finding

261
00:17:28.960 --> 00:17:30.840
a kidnapped special agent.
and I'll make an exception.

262
00:17:33.090 --> 00:17:34.880
Hold on a second.

263
00:17:40.640 --> 00:17:41.850
Hey. are you okay?

264
00:17:43.350 --> 00:17:44.350
Dad.

265
00:17:45.980 --> 00:17:48.020
You usually don't do work
the third day after chemo.

266
00:17:48.850 --> 00:17:49.860
I'm good.

267
00:17:49.940 --> 00:17:52.320
Daddy. did you see Max's new perm?

268
00:17:52.400 --> 00:17:53.780
His what? His perm?

269
00:17:53.860 --> 00:17:56.400
All right. it's a light perm.

270
00:17:56.490 --> 00:17:58.610
Guys are doing it now.
It's not that big of a deal.

271
00:17:58.700 --> 00:17:59.990
Yeah.

272
00:18:00.070 --> 00:18:01.280
Okay.

273
00:18:01.370 --> 00:18:02.490
Yeah. it's…

274
00:18:04.080 --> 00:18:05.160
it's very boingy.

275
00:18:05.250 --> 00:18:08.210
I like you're trying things.

276
00:18:08.290 --> 00:18:11.710
Okay. Here. This is promising.

277
00:18:11.790 --> 00:18:14.170
Right. there's our mysterious lady
in the sun hat.

278
00:18:14.260 --> 00:18:17.880
and we don't care that we can't see
your face because we can see…

279
00:18:21.390 --> 00:18:23.180
There's no plate.
How can there be no plate?

280
00:18:25.770 --> 00:18:28.520
- Sorry. Dad.
- No. no. we don't give up.

281
00:18:28.600 --> 00:18:30.400
We… Aha!

282
00:18:30.480 --> 00:18:32.480
There. it's a sticker.

283
00:18:32.570 --> 00:18:35.230
It's an oil change sticker
and I know that place.

284
00:18:35.320 --> 00:18:37.320
They give discounts to law enforcement.

285
00:18:37.400 --> 00:18:38.400
You think she's a cop?

286
00:18:38.490 --> 00:18:41.410
I think that they have
a location right next to the state prison.

287
00:18:41.490 --> 00:18:44.240
I'd say there's a good chance
she's a correctional officer.

288
00:18:44.740 --> 00:18:48.040
- All right. Dad. let's go.
- Go. Dad. Go. Dad. Go. go. go.

289
00:18:48.120 --> 00:18:49.120
Go. Dad.

290
00:18:57.010 --> 00:18:58.800
May I say something?

291
00:18:59.630 --> 00:19:03.050
You were right. That was delicious.

292
00:19:03.140 --> 00:19:06.060
- Mm. mm. mm!
- Mm-hmm!

293
00:19:06.140 --> 00:19:07.560
Mm!

294
00:19:07.640 --> 00:19:10.850
Family recipe.

295
00:19:11.770 --> 00:19:15.360
So. Ms. Susan.
how'd you two lovebirds hit it off?

296
00:19:15.440 --> 00:19:17.820
I'm guessing you a correctional officer?

297
00:19:18.400 --> 00:19:21.360
The way you've handled us
and your attention to detail.

298
00:19:21.450 --> 00:19:25.120
Well. started in tiny ways.

299
00:19:25.200 --> 00:19:30.460
That's how the strongest love is built.
Slowly. over time.

300
00:19:31.120 --> 00:19:37.170
Little hellos on his way to
the prison library and the secret notes.

301
00:19:39.260 --> 00:19:43.260
Who knew a life sentence
would bring a life partner?

302
00:19:46.310 --> 00:19:47.520
Hmm?

303
00:19:47.600 --> 00:19:50.560
Well. I'm sure the other women
felt as special as I did.

304
00:19:56.900 --> 00:20:03.610
But unlike them. we had time together.
stolen moments that added up over years.

305
00:20:03.700 --> 00:20:09.080
What began
as a dalliance became. ooh. undeniable.

306
00:20:09.910 --> 00:20:11.080
Oh!

307
00:20:13.670 --> 00:20:19.170
Ms. Susan. is it possible
that this entire situation

308
00:20:19.260 --> 00:20:22.050
is just all a terrible misunderstanding?

309
00:20:22.130 --> 00:20:24.140
Well. I don't know if I believe him.

310
00:20:24.220 --> 00:20:29.520
I'm highly specialized in reading people
and interrogation. and his words.

311
00:20:30.390 --> 00:20:32.100
- they ring genuine to me.
- Mm.

312
00:20:33.560 --> 00:20:35.310
I love you.

313
00:20:39.110 --> 00:20:41.150
Why don't we play roses and thorns?

314
00:20:42.360 --> 00:20:44.030
What's roses and thorns?

315
00:20:44.660 --> 00:20:47.830
We do it after every dinner in my family.

316
00:20:47.910 --> 00:20:49.370
You'll catch on. okay?

317
00:20:49.450 --> 00:20:54.920
My rose is I finally
get to be with my Jimmy.

318
00:20:55.000 --> 00:20:57.790
away from everyone. with just our love.

319
00:20:58.710 --> 00:21:02.630
And my thorn is having
to use the stun cuff on you.

320
00:21:03.380 --> 00:21:04.430
And you.

321
00:21:05.050 --> 00:21:06.800
Okay. how about you. Jimmy?

322
00:21:07.390 --> 00:21:09.220
What's your rose? What's your thorn?

323
00:21:14.100 --> 00:21:15.730
Uh…

324
00:21:16.440 --> 00:21:19.230
I'm all thorns right now. Suzie.

325
00:21:19.320 --> 00:21:24.150
I didn't spend a year planning
and risking my life on a prison escape.

326
00:21:24.900 --> 00:21:28.370
only to be captured
by a menopausal harpy with thick shoes.

327
00:21:28.450 --> 00:21:33.330
I can only think of one rose
and it is a fantasy

328
00:21:34.120 --> 00:21:36.210
of sewing your mouth shut.

329
00:21:38.250 --> 00:21:40.420
Oh. my.

330
00:21:42.550 --> 00:21:44.590
Just for that. no dessert.

331
00:21:50.600 --> 00:21:54.140
You can be so bossy and demeaning.

332
00:21:54.230 --> 00:21:58.100
I want you to learn that I deserve
more than just a lover.

333
00:21:58.190 --> 00:22:00.610
I deserve a partner.

334
00:22:03.690 --> 00:22:07.860
Figure it out. Before you don't have
any more fingers to lose.

335
00:22:09.160 --> 00:22:10.450
Come here.

336
00:22:22.800 --> 00:22:23.800
Oh.

337
00:22:24.760 --> 00:22:25.760
All better.

338
00:22:27.170 --> 00:22:28.220
Okay.

339
00:22:31.720 --> 00:22:32.720
Get some rest.

340
00:22:35.310 --> 00:22:37.270
Momma's got some errands to run.

341
00:22:37.350 --> 00:22:40.020
Just never ends
with taking care of you two.

342
00:22:48.150 --> 00:22:50.360
What do you think about a throat rip now?

343
00:22:51.570 --> 00:22:56.450
I'm guessing the finger that you had
her wrapped around is the one she cut off?

344
00:22:56.540 --> 00:22:58.580
Where did you learn that dopey prayer?

345
00:22:58.660 --> 00:23:00.370
Foster care.

346
00:23:00.460 --> 00:23:03.540
It's also where I learned how to keep
a bad marriage from getting me killed.

347
00:23:05.090 --> 00:23:06.510
What does that mean?

348
00:23:06.590 --> 00:23:07.920
She's out of range.

349
00:23:08.420 --> 00:23:10.260
I'm guessing it's 150 yards.

350
00:23:11.180 --> 00:23:13.050
Which puts her outside the building.

351
00:23:17.270 --> 00:23:19.890
- Oh!
- I'm getting this condenser out.

352
00:23:20.730 --> 00:23:23.770
- Then we crawl through...
- You little scamp.

353
00:23:25.320 --> 00:23:27.070
Don't give me nicknames.

354
00:23:28.900 --> 00:23:31.410
Okay. Okay. here's the employee list
from the warden.

355
00:23:31.490 --> 00:23:35.200
It's 400 names. 123 of them are female.

356
00:23:35.990 --> 00:23:37.700
We can narrow it down. Ow.

357
00:23:37.790 --> 00:23:39.830
You good?

358
00:23:39.910 --> 00:23:41.920
Ah. it's just a cramp.
I'm not drinking enough water.

359
00:23:42.000 --> 00:23:44.420
Hey. how many of them drive pickup trucks?

360
00:23:44.500 --> 00:23:45.840
Can you figure that out?

361
00:23:45.920 --> 00:23:47.880
Watch how my fingers fly.

362
00:23:49.340 --> 00:23:52.340
Watching you type is like
watching a dog dance on its hind legs.

363
00:23:53.300 --> 00:23:56.970
Thank you. And we are down to 23 women.

364
00:23:57.060 --> 00:23:58.680
You know. 23 is manageable.

365
00:23:58.770 --> 00:24:00.390
Okay. let me get this list
to Faith and Caleb

366
00:24:00.480 --> 00:24:01.940
then we can coordinate interviews.

367
00:24:02.480 --> 00:24:03.560
You ready. Polaski?

368
00:24:08.860 --> 00:24:10.990
Just… give me a sec.

369
00:24:11.070 --> 00:24:12.860
You know what else feels like a cramp?

370
00:24:12.950 --> 00:24:13.950
A contraction.

371
00:24:14.030 --> 00:24:15.870
What. you want me to get it checked out?

372
00:24:18.910 --> 00:24:20.790
Fine. I'll get it checked out.
It's nothing.

373
00:24:21.370 --> 00:24:23.040
- You want me to come with?
- No. no.

374
00:24:23.750 --> 00:24:26.380
Keep looking for sun hat lady
and keep me posted.

375
00:24:31.550 --> 00:24:32.630
One more.

376
00:24:33.720 --> 00:24:36.050
Look. when I get back.
I'm gonna tell you a story about the time

377
00:24:36.140 --> 00:24:38.510
that me and this guy
were working a prison transport.

378
00:24:38.600 --> 00:24:40.600
Some idiot tried to carjack us.

379
00:24:41.230 --> 00:24:43.310
- Can't wait.
- I'll be right back.

380
00:24:46.440 --> 00:24:48.110
You said this guy could be a shortcut?

381
00:24:48.190 --> 00:24:49.440
He's my contact.

382
00:24:49.530 --> 00:24:50.690
Let me play him.

383
00:24:54.990 --> 00:24:56.780
I can't believe Will didn't call me.

384
00:24:57.570 --> 00:25:01.870
Yeah. I'm sure that he feels
completely responsible for Calvin.

385
00:25:05.210 --> 00:25:10.130
Look. He takes a long time
to open up to someone.

386
00:25:10.710 --> 00:25:13.170
I'm sure what he went through
in his childhood didn't help.

387
00:25:16.140 --> 00:25:18.970
So. you said kidnapping
with two victims. huh?

388
00:25:19.470 --> 00:25:21.270
That made me think.
a couple of weeks back.

389
00:25:21.350 --> 00:25:23.980
a pair of stun cuffs went
missing with the remote.

390
00:25:24.480 --> 00:25:26.480
That's like ten grand in value.

391
00:25:26.560 --> 00:25:28.980
Warden couldn't figure it out.
swept the whole thing under the rug.

392
00:25:29.650 --> 00:25:30.730
That's all I can tell you.

393
00:25:33.070 --> 00:25:34.610
We have a list of names.

394
00:25:34.700 --> 00:25:37.700
Maybe you could take a look at it
and see if anyone makes sense for this.

395
00:25:46.000 --> 00:25:48.830
Hmm. Well. this one here. I know her.

396
00:25:49.420 --> 00:25:51.250
She would have had access.

397
00:25:54.050 --> 00:25:55.220
Susan Barno.

398
00:26:04.770 --> 00:26:06.520
Hmm.

399
00:26:07.270 --> 00:26:09.400
She is absolutely fine.

400
00:26:09.480 --> 00:26:11.270
Those are Braxton-Hicks contractions.

401
00:26:11.360 --> 00:26:13.400
Perfectly normal
in the second and third trimester.

402
00:26:13.480 --> 00:26:14.900
The third too? That's good.

403
00:26:14.990 --> 00:26:16.200
Something to look forward to.

404
00:26:16.280 --> 00:26:18.360
Well. there's also. you know. the baby.

405
00:26:18.450 --> 00:26:19.620
- Right.
- Stay hydrated.

406
00:26:19.700 --> 00:26:22.580
Try shifting positions or walking around
if they get too uncomfortable.

407
00:26:22.660 --> 00:26:24.160
Okay. Thanks.

408
00:26:24.790 --> 00:26:25.790
- Thank you.
- Yep.

409
00:26:25.870 --> 00:26:27.160
It's a relief.

410
00:26:27.250 --> 00:26:29.420
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Can you check that for me?

411
00:26:30.880 --> 00:26:32.420
It's 7834.

412
00:26:33.500 --> 00:26:34.670
Phone code?

413
00:26:34.760 --> 00:26:37.220
- What a gesture of intimacy.
- Is it work?

414
00:26:38.630 --> 00:26:40.050
Why. are you working?

415
00:26:40.140 --> 00:26:42.510
You know I can't sit this one out.

416
00:26:44.470 --> 00:26:47.310
Hey. how about I…
how about I pick up a pizza…

417
00:26:47.390 --> 00:26:49.440
- Barno's? Barno's?
- …on the way home. Detroit style.

418
00:26:49.520 --> 00:26:52.310
- Hell yeah. Barno's. I feel like.
- Yeah? Good.

419
00:26:52.400 --> 00:26:54.480
You remember Barno's packaged foods?

420
00:26:54.570 --> 00:26:58.240
I feel like they had a big warehouse
in. like. Dunwoody.

421
00:26:58.320 --> 00:27:00.280
What the hell are you doing. Angie?

422
00:27:01.620 --> 00:27:02.780
We are trying to find Will.

423
00:27:02.870 --> 00:27:05.330
He doesn't need you right now.
Our baby needs you.

424
00:27:06.040 --> 00:27:08.370
Okay. feel free to keep
telling me what I can and cannot do.

425
00:27:08.460 --> 00:27:10.250
No. I'm telling you what you should do.

426
00:27:10.330 --> 00:27:12.290
You should rest. You should stay hydrated.

427
00:27:12.380 --> 00:27:15.210
APB. GBI. marshals. sheriffs.

428
00:27:15.300 --> 00:27:18.300
everybody with a badge in Atlanta
is out there looking for him.

429
00:27:23.430 --> 00:27:24.970
Wish I could be like you.

430
00:27:25.850 --> 00:27:27.600
- Okay.
- No. no. listen.

431
00:27:27.680 --> 00:27:30.440
Really. I wish I had grown up just…

432
00:27:31.940 --> 00:27:33.730
living my life.

433
00:27:36.020 --> 00:27:37.480
No constant fear.

434
00:27:39.030 --> 00:27:40.860
No wondering if…

435
00:27:42.610 --> 00:27:46.830
anyone is going to come and save you.

436
00:27:49.790 --> 00:27:51.160
Will has come.

437
00:27:51.250 --> 00:27:52.500
He's always come.

438
00:27:52.580 --> 00:27:54.210
He has saved me…

439
00:27:55.880 --> 00:27:59.380
over and over.

440
00:28:00.920 --> 00:28:02.220
He's my family.

441
00:28:05.550 --> 00:28:07.680
You're right. You're right.

442
00:28:07.760 --> 00:28:09.980
I grew up feeling safe.

443
00:28:12.100 --> 00:28:13.980
It's not wrong to want that for my child.

444
00:28:15.190 --> 00:28:18.320
This is your family. I'm your family.

445
00:28:22.650 --> 00:28:23.860
I'll see you at home.

446
00:28:30.410 --> 00:28:31.540
Okay.

447
00:28:33.620 --> 00:28:35.580
Isn't it funny how we ended up like this.

448
00:28:35.670 --> 00:28:40.380
Classic father-son bonding.
using tools and our muscles.

449
00:28:40.460 --> 00:28:43.300
We are not bonding. okay?
And you are not my father.

450
00:28:43.380 --> 00:28:44.640
Well. almost was.

451
00:28:45.430 --> 00:28:47.430
Your mother and I were very close.

452
00:28:47.930 --> 00:28:49.180
When Lucy started…

453
00:28:49.770 --> 00:28:51.560
- Hey! Whoa!
- I can't.

454
00:28:57.520 --> 00:29:00.070
- Damn it!
- We have to switch places.

455
00:29:00.150 --> 00:29:02.320
You have nine fingers.
What are you gonna do?

456
00:29:02.400 --> 00:29:04.320
- I can't hold you.
- No way I'm letting you

457
00:29:04.400 --> 00:29:06.160
- hold anything sharp.
- We have to switch places.

458
00:29:06.240 --> 00:29:07.530
Can't get leverage on the last thing.

459
00:29:07.620 --> 00:29:08.830
- We need a new angle.
- How do we get…

460
00:29:08.910 --> 00:29:10.370
Hey. What are we gonna do?

461
00:29:11.160 --> 00:29:14.370
I don't know. okay?

462
00:29:15.920 --> 00:29:17.960
Don't lose your head.

463
00:29:19.290 --> 00:29:21.170
I'm not dying here with you.

464
00:29:24.840 --> 00:29:26.050
Oh. God!

465
00:29:30.060 --> 00:29:31.560
You deserve better.

466
00:29:36.140 --> 00:29:37.400
What was that?

467
00:29:38.020 --> 00:29:39.520
Is that an apology?

468
00:29:39.610 --> 00:29:43.490
No. no. An observation.

469
00:29:43.570 --> 00:29:45.240
A feeling.

470
00:29:45.320 --> 00:29:46.530
You…

471
00:29:48.070 --> 00:29:50.410
You're brilliant. loyal.

472
00:29:50.490 --> 00:29:51.870
You don't stop.

473
00:29:51.950 --> 00:29:53.410
I admire you.

474
00:29:55.660 --> 00:29:56.790
I love you.

475
00:29:57.920 --> 00:29:59.500
Oh. God.

476
00:29:59.580 --> 00:30:03.510
I hated you. I hated you for…
for taking Lucy away.

477
00:30:06.630 --> 00:30:09.300
I see her in you.

478
00:30:11.560 --> 00:30:12.930
But she had balance.

479
00:30:15.140 --> 00:30:16.810
You run from the dark.

480
00:30:18.480 --> 00:30:20.440
That's why it chases you.

481
00:30:28.410 --> 00:30:30.910
You ever regret what you did to my mother?

482
00:30:33.490 --> 00:30:34.870
Yes.

483
00:30:41.710 --> 00:30:43.210
I was gonna kill you.

484
00:30:43.710 --> 00:30:49.430
Oh. so there is a monster
in there after all. Yeah.

485
00:30:53.350 --> 00:30:54.720
What are you doing?

486
00:30:55.350 --> 00:30:56.600
No. no. no.

487
00:30:57.730 --> 00:30:59.440
Hey. hey. hey.

488
00:30:59.520 --> 00:31:01.230
Easy. easy.

489
00:31:06.150 --> 00:31:07.740
What are you doing? Hey.

490
00:31:09.360 --> 00:31:11.870
What are you doing? Stop. stop. stop.

491
00:31:11.950 --> 00:31:13.620
We're gonna tip this bastard over

492
00:31:13.700 --> 00:31:17.160
because you're not gonna be the last
person to ever say anything nice to me.

493
00:31:17.910 --> 00:31:20.330
Now get up! Let's go!

494
00:31:23.090 --> 00:31:25.880
One. two. three.

495
00:31:30.470 --> 00:31:31.470
Again. go.

496
00:31:34.510 --> 00:31:37.350
He's here. Ormewood. I can feel it.

497
00:31:37.430 --> 00:31:40.230
Caleb and Faith are ten minutes
out. SWAT's right behind them.

498
00:31:41.020 --> 00:31:43.360
All right. I'm gonna keep an eye out.

499
00:31:43.940 --> 00:31:45.270
Don't do anything stupid.

500
00:31:45.360 --> 00:31:46.860
- I'm serious.
- Yep.

501
00:31:52.860 --> 00:31:54.410
I've told you about Will.

502
00:31:57.200 --> 00:31:58.540
He needs to meet you.

503
00:31:59.870 --> 00:32:01.160
We know what we're doing.

504
00:32:17.470 --> 00:32:18.770
Come on.

505
00:32:21.140 --> 00:32:22.480
She's back. We have to stop.

506
00:32:24.480 --> 00:32:26.270
No. We're doing this. Let's go.

507
00:33:30.050 --> 00:33:32.590
Enough of this misbehaving.

508
00:33:34.720 --> 00:33:37.470
Who's gonna put that
trailer right side up again. huh?

509
00:33:42.350 --> 00:33:43.430
You.

510
00:33:43.930 --> 00:33:45.190
You're the bad apple.

511
00:33:45.270 --> 00:33:50.110
My Jimmy is a genius in many ways
but he's not mechanical.

512
00:33:52.690 --> 00:33:54.900
- Will.
- Angie. get out of here.

513
00:33:55.860 --> 00:33:57.240
No!

514
00:34:01.490 --> 00:34:02.870
Who the hell is Angie?

515
00:34:03.700 --> 00:34:06.750
I swear to God. Jimmy.
if she's got your ring on her finger…

516
00:34:08.460 --> 00:34:11.500
There is a limit to what I will take.

517
00:34:19.550 --> 00:34:21.390
Angie. where are you?

518
00:34:27.350 --> 00:34:29.440
Damn it.

519
00:34:33.780 --> 00:34:37.490
You brought such calamity upon our family.

520
00:34:37.570 --> 00:34:38.860
No!

521
00:34:38.950 --> 00:34:40.700
No!

522
00:34:47.500 --> 00:34:50.460
Oh. no. Jimmy!

523
00:34:50.540 --> 00:34:54.000
Oh. God. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

524
00:34:54.090 --> 00:34:57.260
No!

525
00:35:15.530 --> 00:35:17.860
- Police.
- Police. Get on the ground.

526
00:35:17.940 --> 00:35:20.110
- Drop your weapon.
- Get on the ground.

527
00:35:25.330 --> 00:35:26.370
I got cover.

528
00:35:39.920 --> 00:35:41.010
See you soon.

529
00:35:49.100 --> 00:35:50.350
Will.

530
00:36:06.870 --> 00:36:07.910
Hi.

531
00:36:09.160 --> 00:36:10.160
Did I wake you?

532
00:36:13.380 --> 00:36:14.670
Yesterday scared me. Angie.

533
00:36:15.420 --> 00:36:17.000
I mean. it really scared me.

534
00:36:17.090 --> 00:36:18.420
I know.

535
00:36:18.510 --> 00:36:20.340
Do you? I'm not…

536
00:36:20.420 --> 00:36:21.840
I'm not challenging you.

537
00:36:23.180 --> 00:36:24.590
I just wonder if you understand.

538
00:36:32.890 --> 00:36:33.900
Tell me.

539
00:36:34.940 --> 00:36:38.110
I've never been held captive
by a deranged serial killer.

540
00:36:38.190 --> 00:36:40.280
Well. it's a pretty exclusive club.

541
00:36:41.030 --> 00:36:43.150
But I do know what it's
like to lose the woman I love.

542
00:36:45.160 --> 00:36:46.160
Permanent loss.

543
00:36:47.410 --> 00:36:48.660
Also a crappy club.

544
00:36:49.200 --> 00:36:52.290
- We gotta join better clubs.
- Mm.

545
00:36:53.330 --> 00:36:56.500
I do get it. I'm walking into a job
where anything can happen.

546
00:36:58.290 --> 00:36:59.340
Every day.

547
00:37:01.090 --> 00:37:05.090
- That's just the job.
- And you do it fearlessly. It's so hot.

548
00:37:05.800 --> 00:37:08.720
But now it's not just you
heading into the danger.

549
00:37:08.810 --> 00:37:11.770
I think my womb might be
the safest place in Atlanta.

550
00:37:12.640 --> 00:37:14.190
I'm like a baby panic room.

551
00:37:18.820 --> 00:37:22.900
Life has been on my back since I was five.

552
00:37:24.530 --> 00:37:26.740
It's tried a thousand ways
to take me down.

553
00:37:28.830 --> 00:37:29.950
I'm still standing.

554
00:37:32.290 --> 00:37:33.830
Can you trust me?

555
00:37:36.620 --> 00:37:38.540
You trust me to take care of her?

556
00:37:39.540 --> 00:37:41.460
That's what this
stage of love is. I guess.

557
00:37:43.880 --> 00:37:46.720
Not a lot of songs about the pain
in the ass parts of a relationship.

558
00:37:46.800 --> 00:37:49.350
- The baby-making part. so many songs.
- So many songs.

559
00:37:49.430 --> 00:37:50.510
Yeah.

560
00:37:53.770 --> 00:37:58.350
I think. though. that this stuff
is what really matters.

561
00:37:59.690 --> 00:38:00.690
Yeah.

562
00:38:04.900 --> 00:38:09.950
And dot. Let's see if I get this right.

563
00:38:10.030 --> 00:38:11.280
Just a dot. no L.

564
00:38:11.370 --> 00:38:12.580
Wow. guys.

565
00:38:12.660 --> 00:38:14.330
We should get
you two to make all the meals.

566
00:38:14.410 --> 00:38:16.870
Yeah. I'd settle for kitchen clean-up.

567
00:38:16.960 --> 00:38:19.130
Well. I put in the blueberries
and the chocolate chips.

568
00:38:19.210 --> 00:38:21.040
- Nice. Whoa!
- Chocolate chips!

569
00:38:21.130 --> 00:38:22.630
Those things don't really
go together. but…

570
00:38:22.710 --> 00:38:23.710
Yes. they do.

571
00:38:23.800 --> 00:38:27.260
- No. they don't.
- Hi. Hey. uh. where are we today?

572
00:38:28.220 --> 00:38:29.300
About a three.

573
00:38:29.970 --> 00:38:31.010
You wanna go?

574
00:38:31.100 --> 00:38:33.180
I'll cover for you
and put them in some Tupperware.

575
00:38:33.850 --> 00:38:35.730
I'm okay. Thank you.

576
00:38:37.230 --> 00:38:38.900
So. how do you like it. Daddy?

577
00:38:38.980 --> 00:38:42.480
Mm! It's delicious. baby.

578
00:38:42.570 --> 00:38:44.360
How much longer are you on desk duty?

579
00:38:44.440 --> 00:38:45.940
Couple more weeks. I hope.

580
00:38:46.030 --> 00:38:49.660
I mean. don't get me wrong.
I am an unexpected computer genius.

581
00:38:50.570 --> 00:38:52.370
but my best work is not behind a desk.

582
00:38:52.450 --> 00:38:53.950
We're going with genius. are we?

583
00:38:54.040 --> 00:38:56.750
It's just… It's been nice
to FaceTime you during the day.

584
00:38:57.460 --> 00:38:59.750
Yeah. and you come home
a lot more when you say you will.

585
00:39:00.630 --> 00:39:01.630
Oh.

586
00:39:03.670 --> 00:39:06.300
Well. those sound like easy things
to keep going

587
00:39:06.380 --> 00:39:08.470
once your dad is back in the field. right?

588
00:39:10.010 --> 00:39:11.180
Yeah.

589
00:39:14.680 --> 00:39:16.600
So. who has the syrup?

590
00:39:16.680 --> 00:39:18.640
- Ah. Here.
- Thank ya.

591
00:39:18.730 --> 00:39:21.440
- So. when can I drink coffee?
- I hear you like it black. yeah?

592
00:39:21.940 --> 00:39:24.190
No. I'm kidding. I'm kidding.
You're not gonna want it.

593
00:39:30.150 --> 00:39:33.700
Amanda.
glad to hear your golden boy is safe.

594
00:39:33.780 --> 00:39:34.870
How's he doing?

595
00:39:34.950 --> 00:39:36.620
He's been through worse.

596
00:39:37.910 --> 00:39:39.370
You forget something in my office?

597
00:39:39.460 --> 00:39:41.670
Yeah. I spoke to
the director this morning.

598
00:39:41.750 --> 00:39:43.960
We had a good mind meld
about great leaders

599
00:39:44.040 --> 00:39:46.420
who couldn't see when their time was done.

600
00:39:47.460 --> 00:39:48.550
Interesting.

601
00:39:49.380 --> 00:39:52.260
Our conversations are
usually about unqualified men

602
00:39:52.340 --> 00:39:54.800
pushing themselves into spaces
where they don't belong.

603
00:39:55.850 --> 00:39:59.100
You know there's no shame
in the next chapter. Amanda.

604
00:40:00.270 --> 00:40:01.980
Are you looking for a fight. Bill?

605
00:40:02.560 --> 00:40:03.610
You'll get one.

606
00:40:10.320 --> 00:40:12.160
I hope this isn't a wellness check.

607
00:40:13.570 --> 00:40:14.950
Just dropping in on family.

608
00:40:16.700 --> 00:40:17.870
How's Calvin?

609
00:40:19.080 --> 00:40:20.080
He's fine.

610
00:40:21.290 --> 00:40:22.370
How about you?

611
00:40:23.830 --> 00:40:26.460
Well. seeing my therapist tomorrow.

612
00:40:27.960 --> 00:40:29.340
Dr. Roach.

613
00:40:29.920 --> 00:40:32.720
She has a whole plan for us.

614
00:40:32.800 --> 00:40:35.550
- Wants me to try Frisbee golf.
- Oh!

615
00:40:36.390 --> 00:40:39.100
Sounds helpful.

616
00:40:39.180 --> 00:40:43.190
Yeah. She's peculiar. Frisbee golf.

617
00:40:43.770 --> 00:40:45.520
I mean. why are we mashing those together?

618
00:40:45.610 --> 00:40:46.940
Keep it simple.

619
00:40:47.020 --> 00:40:48.150
Exactly.

620
00:40:51.400 --> 00:40:55.200
We found your car headed in
the opposite direction of GBI.

621
00:41:01.500 --> 00:41:04.460
I missed a turn and got lost.

622
00:41:05.880 --> 00:41:10.300
Unfamiliar terrain and dyslexia.
It's a bad combination.

623
00:41:17.930 --> 00:41:20.850
Listen.
I don't wanna force a conversation.

624
00:41:21.600 --> 00:41:23.980
but I want you to know
you can call me anytime.

625
00:41:25.020 --> 00:41:26.440
For anything.

626
00:41:27.810 --> 00:41:29.150
Hmm.

627
00:41:31.070 --> 00:41:33.240
I hope it brings you
relief that he's gone.

628
00:41:42.040 --> 00:41:43.750
The world is a safer place.

629
00:41:48.750 --> 00:41:51.050
I was gonna make some café con leche.

630
00:41:52.420 --> 00:41:53.720
It takes me a few minutes.

631
00:41:56.680 --> 00:41:57.890
You want one?

632
00:41:58.470 --> 00:41:59.600
Yeah.

633
00:42:00.640 --> 00:42:02.100
I've got all day.

634
00:42:02.640 --> 00:42:03.730
All day?

635
00:42:03.810 --> 00:42:06.230
You got somebody better
you want to sit around with?

636
00:42:09.360 --> 00:42:10.480
I suppose not.
